Sec. 61.006. LABELING OF TREATED SEED. (a) Seed that has been
subjected to a treatment, or to which a substance has been applied,
for the purpose of reducing, controlling, or repelling disease
organisms, insects, or other pests that attack seeds or seedlings
shall be labeled in accordance with rules of the department.
(b) The public hearing required by Section 61.002 of this code
for rulemaking under this section shall be conducted in Austin.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1128, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

